condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :General Conditions, Sec. 5.08 (c) | Description :The Borrower/JSIF will prepare a Completion Report at the endof the project. | Due Date :31-Jul-2016

Finance Agreement :LA, Sch. II, Sec. 1, B, 1 | Description :The Borrower will establish and maintain the Inter-Ministerial ProjectSteering Committee under TORs acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :15-Feb-2010

Finance Agreement :LA, Sch. II, Sec. 1, B, 3 | Description :The Borrower/JSIF will sign MOUs with MOA&F/RADA and with MOT/TPDCodescribing their roles in project implementation. | Due Date :09-Feb-2010
Finance Agreement :LA, Sch. II, Sec. 1, D, 1, a | Description :The Borrower/JSIF will carry out the Project in compliance with theOM. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, 1, b, i | Description :The JSIF will maintain the PMT within JSIF. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, 1, c | Description :The Borrower/JSIF will complete a mid-term review report to be made availablebefore the mid-term evaluation mission, in accordancewith a TOR acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :15-Dec-2012
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, 1, d | Description :The JSIF will develop business and implementation plan templates acceptableto the Bank prior to subproject selection. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, 1, e | Description :The JSIF will select and contract subproject formulators within three monthsof the date of effectiveness. | Due Date :30-Jan-2010
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, 1, f | Description :The Borrower/JSIF will establish the REEC with composition acceptable to thebank prior to subproject selection. | Due Date :30-Apr-2010
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, 1, h | Description :JSIF will maintain a MIS. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, 1, i | Description :JSIF will conduct an annual audit of sample subprojects to learn lessons fromthe application of the EMF. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A, b, ii, A | Description :Within one month of the Effectiveness date, JSIF shall ensure that theAgriculture Specialist and Tourism Specialist have been appointed, and that the M&E specialist will be appointed within 4 months. |Due Date :25-Feb-2010
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. 1, A,1, g | Description :JSIF will provide training in environmental management, including applicationof the EMF. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Sec. I, A, 2 | Description :JSIF will adopt a Project communications strategy by November 30, 2009. | DueDate :30-Nov-2009
